r and overtake human global health under most welfare-range estimates. An animals person won&#x27;t think only people in their community matter, so this assumption requires far_away_humans. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1lW1z2jgQx7%2FKDnM3hQwhNj3mWjq8gOA8TOk1k9Lr3IRMIuw11lWWPJKM40vz3W9lEx4CvIrDrn5a7f7%2F0nMjwpjlwp6rCBv9xtkZDAYDmGrGJVgFoWb%2FlfRRSJjlXc%2F%2FAwqlRbTkWEDhP3ShaazKoNtyy2aSlg%2BNydPMciUhTIjSBw8yplWYcCYcxP%2FYBR9iph9YwcqHJE%2BZNK%2BBLjDJUybMg1EpFgmzFTRgYQJsQ%2BYGGNyUNqHvmAsEqnYTNmdgaSWwKDJt0EhH5BINKF3BNJ5SQSxFi5ob%2Bt0mWNf6zkCcy7BifIJQpZkyXC42CbRWRkhE%2BombimYskxETSiKk1EPRgcd1i4LloyvVLcenDENLC5dM5AgqrgibbnYq2AiNhXleQu62cQsNbh%2BsD1NiXbmWIUyQLXKsF14GfwW3w2kwhnkJC5SomcVOVr5ODSNudzp0QsE2SGXrOlwTiVSxxlxTqYBx7P5Qh9F1X%2BkFtSfTNB1dwpy2iHnI6bsNo%2BDi621Ax9dMVIQC%2BSKx1DlqhlBORwl%2FrIcm1EIqTROGj97vcH4NTaXpqKcqPk3ZQnKbRwijr9PgvEX1GJVnn7kNE5RjJsob1N9NBAN4nkmADFUm8ApFhtE64nW8ntvQ6%2FRcToFCzJEquaTpOUSd4vl1jue7pFDlkrQQs9DmTIyY%2FPl3NSSX%2Bv7ITicH0CfQ9OH0GK41ky8zuYh2DuJqWdXrdWeSpfHbcLeOUqGMp3tr%2FXXUJmInWkXee9TDItsNeC7S8zyKFVxE83xhdhJ66wTKYELEuFdzBfcpTFYolNo%2F0yrBqyG1h%2B%2BK8XDyD7AlameEjAT%2B231%2FW13RjvIsT1fm3CgrVBQk3aG0bwxEy9mbqwey3BonYG6dlkLljDuAOzfSZ6BmYx9mjYkKSY1OafCzltqs0YYiWh%2BpDyky2TyoxRYN3YeX9i7yki%2BxdpEoD8O2ZXCc8YMkBu5%2BpeNobktoDr9ctA4Td6RzGDm8%2FgJncL5iBdJqzOhCw1ybhGdHsNuiO4zdu5IOk3YE6kjOql7vzw%2F7xG8JXTMZ0PHpmUC40epf6uWRsWzLu8Lu4X6QyumFMMQw0EzqUjO6aklIEZojDd33xmH6cDK5CMZHuvfGPUcI12BYjG6%2Bt7Wf4JYufqbD5Ehte7bbgO%2Bd3TRdOu7hGsCEG9vRSJ4z2Kz%2BMUrbUdms7dCG519Pv%2BCps7XHS4uuqrl7iQawAt159ysXTw%2B%2BZdOr628bK%2FbBPdzkOgPz1weNTM6pCkNG3HoeaQeXsb37TDZe%2FgcjXOiM" id="w1_2"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#e6e2c0;strokeColor=#b0a04a;fontColor=#3a3410;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="720" y="462" width="236" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Future humans count&lt;br&gt;(discounted)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;▼ 19 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Future people are inside the circle, but with a positive pure-time discount rate — the moderate longtermist position. A modest discount is enough to keep present, measurable global health competitive with future-protecting work; remove it (the next assumption) and the astronomical numbers take over. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_3.drawio" id="w1_2_3"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f2e3b3;strokeColor=#c9a72a;fontColor=#57450e;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="867" y="701" width="172" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5]&lt;br&gt;→ Wild insects (humane pesticides)&lt;br&gt;(Bob Fischer, Brian Tomasik)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. Under RP medians a chicken&#x27;s welfare range is a third of a human&#x27;s, not a fiftieth, and wild/soil invertebrates carry significant aggregate (nematode) weight, so invertebrate work dominates. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 animals_matter_a_lot" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJyFVV1z6jYQ%2FSs7TDuFDCGGlIdLhwcIzseU25vJpb3TCRki7DVWryx5JBnHzc1%2F78omfAQzfYrDrs7unj1Hem2EGLFM2CsVYmPQuLiA4XAIM824BKs