 pesticides)&lt;br&gt;(Brian Tomasik, David Benatar)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + animals_matter_a_lot + meat_eater_problem + net_negative_animal_lives&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The net-negative-lives hypothesis: factory-farmed and wild animals endure more suffering than wellbeing, so their lives are not worth living. Reducing that suffering is worth more per dollar (you are mitigating a catastrophe, not improving a good life), most of all for the astronomical wild-invertebrate populations. Combined with the meat-eater problem it drives human charities firmly net-negative — every human sustained means more net-negative farmed lives. Presupposes counting wild/invertebrate animals, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; and like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans). || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 7 meat_eater_problem → 8 net_negative_animal_lives" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJyFVmtv4kYU%2FStXqFUhJcSGJSRUfMiDPFS2G2VpV1WInMG%2BxtMdz1gz4zg0m%2F%2FeOzbhEUD9gDA%2Bd859nXuH11qEMcuFvVAR1vq1oyMYDAYw1oxLsApCzf6d00MhYZK3Pf8TFEqL6JljAYUftINu0AtOoG6syuCk4Q5PJJGcGZOnmeVKQpgQVx88yJhWYcKZcFT%2BaRt8iJkOWMHmQZKnTJp3oA1M8pQJExiVYpEw%2B450l0jKrEU6HQi1RHuQIrMBfQjJtJoKTN%2BxE5BoA4kzZvkzBhVNIOjZlBEPWZgAW4XNDTC4m9uEnmMuEKggK9gcgXVhsSgyTdBIVeQSDShdkmk8pGxZihQIN%2FTeJlgV4hcDcS7DkuM3CFWaKcPlbGVAZ2WExEiveBWasUxGTCiJkFKbRAuell0YPj%2B5UN1xfMkwtHTwmYkcQcUlw6phrZLsHI2FaT6H3LlxBw2uJ9aHb1xElK0hMgP1sjMIGR3jIY%2FQNCqe6%2BEfw%2Fuz8fASpnOYoURNVW9l83edYMTtRsEOCGyCpG6VYbmaElPJdck1OQOMY%2FdFBUfXDKVnVK1MU6P0HKbkIqYI6LkJ58OrL%2FdDqoZmomQokM8SS4Wk2gjllJvwp6qHQs2k0tRsOPV%2BhotbqCtNmR%2Bq%2BDBlM8ltHiGcfxkPL1xmRuXZ79yGCcpLJuZ3qP80EQzgdSKBiqAygTcoMoyWiNfyus6h1%2Bo6mwKFmCJFck3NdBSViedXNp7vjEKVS5JGzEKbM3HO5Pe%2Fyp45084eTwc7qA%2Bg7sPhPrrGRL5N5CzaSMTFsojXa08kS%2BOPcLtCKVDG062z%2FhK1idhAS6